What occurred during the same time as the beginning of the decline of women in computer science? ~The percentage started to decline in 1984, and by 2010, it had been slashed in half. Women made up just 17.6% of those who graduated from computer and information science majors.
Why does it matter that males had been playing on computers growing up? ~The paucity of women in the field of computing compared to the proportion of men in the area is known as gender inequality in computing.

When are diversity efforts most successful? ~According to research, programs like task forces, diversity managers, and mentoring schemes that need a higher level of ongoing commitment and accountability are the ones that promote workplace diversity the most successfully.
Why do diverse companies perform better? ~Teams with a stronger capacity for innovation and problem-solving will result from the variety of talents, ideas, experiences, and views that employees from all backgrounds bring to the table. 
Give an example of how a diverse company can serve a diverse user base or vise-versa. ~Increased creativity is possible when people from different cultures and backgrounds collaborate.
